The experiment `bow_opt_20260514_175249_run_01` using a Bag of Words (BoW) architecture achieved a reasonable F1 score of 0.7159 and accuracy of 0.75, indicating that the model performed well on the validation set. The use of TF-IDF vectorization with a maximum feature count of 5313 and considering up to trigram features contributed positively to the model's performance. However, the experiment did not explore different hyperparameters such as varying the regularization strength (`logreg_c`) or adjusting the minimum document frequency (`min_df`), which could potentially improve the model further. For the next run, it would be beneficial to conduct a grid search over these hyperparameters and possibly increase the complexity of the model by exploring more advanced architectures like LSTM or BERT to see if they can yield better performance on the task.